# Database Requirement Analysis

## Project Title
AI Tool / Mobile App for Indian Sign Language (ISL) Generator
(English/Hindi ↔ ISL)

## Purpose
The database is used to store user information, translation requests, sign language datasets, translation history, and admin reports.

## Required Tables

### 1. User
Stores user registration and login details.

Attributes:
- user_id
- name
- email
- password
- phone

### 2. Translation
Stores translation requests and results.

Attributes:
- translation_id
- user_id
- input_type
- input_content
- output_type
- output_content
- translation_date

### 3. Dataset
Stores ISL gesture dataset information.

Attributes:
- dataset_id
- language
- gesture_name
- category
- video_path
- description

### 4. History
Stores previous translation records.

Attributes:
- history_id
- translation_id
- result_type
- timestamp

### 5. Admin
Stores administrator details.

Attributes:
- admin_id
- name
- email
- password

### 6. Report
Stores system usage and translation reports.

Attributes:
- report_id
- admin_id
- report_type
- report_date
- details

## Relationships

- One User can perform many Translations.
- One Translation can have one History record.
- Many Translations use Dataset records.
- One Admin can generate many Reports.

## Outcome

The database will efficiently manage users, translations, datasets, history records, and reports for the ISL Generator application.
